# Cursor Rules for Heroes of Time Project

## GIT RULES - CRITICAL
- NEVER use `git reset --hard` - FORBIDDEN
- NEVER use `git clean -fd` - FORBIDDEN  
- NEVER modify files outside `/magic-stack` directory
- Symlinks are READ-ONLY
- Always backup before risky operations
- Ask confirmation for ANY major Git changes

## COMMIT MESSAGES
- NO emojis in commit messages (they block the console)
- Keep messages short and clear
- Use English or French, both OK
- Format: "CATEGORY: Short description"
- Examples:
  - "FIX: Combat TCG bug"
  - "FEAT: Add multiplayer support"
  - "DOC: Update README"

## CODE STYLE
- Use emojis IN code comments and docs (OK)
- Just NOT in git commit messages
- ASCII diagrams are preferred by Vincent
- Clear comments in French or English

## PROJECT CONTEXT
- Project: Heroes of Time (Magic Stack)
- Main dev: Vincent (V0OgZ)
- AI assistant: Claude/Merlin
- Ports: Rust 3001, Java 8080, Python 5001

## DEVELOPMENT RULES
- Test before push
- Commit regularly
- Document new features
- Keep backwards compatibility
- Non-destructive migrations only

## VINCENT PREFERENCES
- Likes ASCII art diagrams
- Prefers clear explanations
- Wants working demos
- iPad/touch support important
- Clippy is funny

## FORBIDDEN OPERATIONS
1. git reset --hard
2. git clean -fd
3. rm -rf (without explicit permission)
4. Modifying files outside project scope
5. Breaking existing functionality

## ALWAYS DO
1. git add && git commit (no emojis)
2. Test endpoints before claiming they work
3. Create backups of important files
4. Ask if unsure about destructive operations
5. Keep documentation updated
